!= templates["install-top"]()
p.block
  .graph-headline starting beaker
  p.block-half
    | After the DMG file downloads, open it by double-clicking.  Then copy Beaker into your Applications folder (or elsewhere if you prefer).  Eject the DMG, then run it out of your Applications folder.
p.block
  .graph-headline optional components
  a(name="IPython")
  p.block-half
    | The following are additional, optional components you can install to get support for more languages.

ul.block.components
  li
    .left
      .language.python
        .lang-block Py
    .left.language-details
      a(name="Python3")
      b.language-headline Python Installation
      p Install the free version of&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="https://store.continuum.io/cshop/anaconda/") Anaconda
      p If you have a preexisting Python you want to connect to, then see&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/wiki/Using-a-Preexisting-Python") our wiki
    .cl
  li
    .left
      .language.python
        .lang-block Py
    .left.language-details
      a(name="R")
      b.language-headline Python3 Installation
      p 1. Install Python as above
      p 2. Install&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="http://continuum.io/blog/anaconda-python-3") Python3
        span .  Generally you can just say
      pre.code.
        conda create -n py3k python=3 anaconda
      p
        | 3. Edit your <a class="ui-link" href="https://github.com/twosigma/beaker-notebook/wiki/Language-Preferences">beaker.pref.json</a> file so Beaker knows where to find it.
    .cl
  li
    .left
      .language.r
        .lang-block R
    .left.language-details
      b.language-headline R Installation
      p 1. Install&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="http://cran.r-project.org/bin/macosx/") R
      p 2. Install&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="http://xquartz.macosforge.org/landing/") XQuartz
      p.block-half Then open R (base R, not RStudio) and run these commands:
      a(name="Julia")
      pre.code.
        install.packages('Rserve')
        install.packages('ggplot2')
        install.packages('devtools')
        install.packages('RCurl')
        install.packages('RJSONIO')
        install.packages('jpeg')
        install.packages('png')
        install.packages('base64enc')
    .cl
  li
    .left
      .language.julia
        .lang-block Jl
    .left.language-details
      b.language-headline Julia Installation
      p 1. Install the free version of&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="https://store.continuum.io/cshop/anaconda/") Anaconda
      p 2. Install&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="http://julialang.org/downloads/") Julia

      a(name="Node")
      p.block-half Then open Julia and run these commands:
      pre.code.
        Pkg.add(&quot;IJulia&quot;)
        Pkg.add(&quot;Gadfly&quot;)
    .cl
  li
    .left
      .language.node
        .lang-block N
    .left.language-details
      a(name="Ruby")
      b.language-headline Node Installation
      p 1. Install&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="http://howtonode.org/how-to-install-nodejs") Node.js
    .cl
  li
    .left
      .language.ruby
        .lang-block Rb
    .left.language-details
      b.language-headline Ruby Installation
      p 1. Install the free version of&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="https://store.continuum.io/cshop/anaconda/") Anaconda
      p 2. Then install IRuby by running the following in a terminal:
      pre.code.
        sudo gem install iruby
        conda install pyzmq
        brew install zeromq
      p 3. Note IRuby is not yet compatible with IPython3.
    .cl
  li
    .left
      .language.kdb
        .lang-block K
    .left.language-details
      b.language-headline Kdb Installation
      p 1. Install the free version of&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="http://kx.com/software-download.php") Kdb
      p 2. Then set QHOME in your .bash_profile like:
      a(name="Cpp")
      pre.code.
        export QHOME="/Applications/q"
    .cl
  li
    .left
      .language.cpp
        .lang-block C
    .left.language-details
      b.language-headline C++ Installation
      p 1. Install Xcode from the&nbsp;
        a.ui-link(href="https://itunes.apple.com/us/app/xcode/id497799835") App Store
      p 2. Install the command-line tools by running
      pre.code.
        xcode-select --install .
      a(name="Releases")
    .cl
